### ============================================
### ERROR CASES / VALIDATION
### ============================================

### Update User - Invalid Email (should return validation error)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation UpdateUser($id: ID!, $input: UpdateUserInput!) { updateUser(id: $id, input: $input) { id name email } }",
  "variables": {
    "id": "user-1",
    "input": {
      "email": "not-an-email"
    }
  }
}

###

### Create Order - Empty Items (should return error from Lambda)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation CreateOrder($input: CreateOrderInput!) { createOrder(input: $input) { id status } }",
  "variables": {
    "input": {
      "userId": "user-1",
      "items": []
    }
  }
}

###

### ============================================
### WITH CUSTOM IDENTITY HEADER
### ============================================

### Create Order with custom identity
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json
X-AppSync-Identity: {"sub": "abc-123", "username": "admin-user"}

{
  "query": "mutation CreateOrder($input: CreateOrderInput!) { createOrder(input: $input) { id userId total status } }",
  "variables": {
    "input": {
      "userId": "user-admin",
      "items": [
        { "productId": "premium-001", "quantity": 1, "price": 199.99 }
      ]
    }
  }
}

###

### ============================================
### INTROSPECTION
### ============================================

### Schema Introspection
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ __schema { queryType { name } mutationType { name } types { name kind } } }"
}

###

### Type Details - User
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ __type(name: \"User\") { name fields { name type { name kind ofType { name } } } } }"
}

